items.title:
de.focus-shift:jollyday 1.6.0 发布, This API determines the holidays for a given year, country/name and eventually state/region. The holiday data is
    stored in XML files (one for each country) and will be read from the classpath. You can provide your own holiday
    calendar XML file or use any of the provided ones.

    Currently, there are over 90 countries supported like the following:
    * United States
    * Germany
    * France
    * India
    * Australia
    * and so on

    Besides, those there will be more special calendars like currently existing NYSE calendar (New York Stock Exchange).

    GitHub project codingstyle (https://github.com/uhafner/codingstyle) - I am using this coding style in my lectures
    about software development at Munich University of Applied Sciences and in all of my open source projects.

    If you want to use this coding style as well, you can use this Maven POM as parent of your own POM. Then you
    get the configuration several static analysis and testing tools for free.
